external_knowledge:
- "seasoned scholars" refers to faculty members who have achieved tenure;
- "blossomed into tenure" indicates that the faculty members have been granted tenure status;
- "fruits of their labor" refers to the total number of publications and the total amount of funding they have received for their research projects.

- "Blossomed with more than 5 research flowers" refers to having more than 5 publications;
- "Gardener of more than 1 research garden" refers to being the principal investigator of more than 1 research project;
- "Mentors more than 3 saplings" refers to advising more than 3 students.

- Tenure status of 1 indicates the faculty member has tenure;
- `department_id` 1 refers to a specific department;
- The average number of publications is calculated across all faculty members.

- A faculty member is analogous to a tree in a garden;
- A research group is analogous to a section of the garden;
- Publications are analogous to flowers blooming on the tree.

- "scholars" refers to faculty members;
- "crowning academic achievements" refers to the highest degree earned by the faculty member;
- "from the most distinguished to the least" indicates the results are ordered in descending order by the highest degree.

sql:
SELECT name, highest_degree
FROM faculty_members
ORDER BY highest_degree DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "shining star" refers to the top-ranked faculty member;
- "research is most generously funded" refers to the highest total funding received for their research projects;
- "contributions to academic literature are plentiful" refers to the highest number of publications;
- "department is the most well-compensated" refers to the highest average salary in the department.

sql:
SELECT name, email, phone
FROM faculty_members
ORDER BY name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- 'leading' refers to the department with the highest total funding amount;
- 'research projects' are projects where a faculty member is the principal investigator;
- 'total funding' is the sum of the funding amounts for all projects in a department.

- "prolific researcher" refers to a faculty member with a high number of publications;
- "recent publications" are those published since January 1, 2020;
- "total number of publications" includes all publications regardless of the publication date.

- "Recent" refers to publications within the last two years;
- "Multiple publications" means the faculty member has published at least two articles in the same journal;
- "Contact details" include the faculty member's email and phone number.

- "Blossomed into a garden of collaborations" refers to having more than one collaboration;
- "Funding shower exceeding a million dollars" refers to the total funding amount being greater than $1,000,000;
- "Most lavishly funded" refers to the project with the highest funding amount.

- "gardener with the most fertile soil" refers to the faculty member with the highest research output;
- "richness of their funding" refers to the total funding allocated to the projects they lead;
- "abundance of their publications" refers to the number of publications they have;
- "number of saplings (students) they nurture" refers to the number of students they advise.
